CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 15, 1967, pg. 24, reads: "Double-Parking Again - That old harassment 'double-parking' or having the 'crust' to stop your car in middle of the street so you can get out and talk to another driver or carry on a conversation with someone in an upstairs window or on the sidewalk still plagues the Hill District. Here, the Courier photographer caught a triple-parking scene which blocks traffic both ways on Wylie Ave."
TitMainTitle: Car double parked on Wylie Avenue, in front of Crawford Grill No. 2, Hill District
